## Wrangler secret labels (names only — never commit values)

**Tier 1 — platform (fixed set, ~8–15 keys):**

- `VAULT_MASTER_KEY` — encrypt `user_secrets` / OAuth tokens in D1
- `TOKEN_SIGNING_KEY` — session + MCP token HMAC
- `PTY_AUTH_TOKEN` — terminal bridge auth
- `AGENTSAM_BRIDGE_KEY` — telemetry ingest / bridge
- `SESSION_SIGNING_SECRET` — optional session crypto
- `INTERNAL_API_SECRET` — internal webhooks / CI hooks
- OAuth: `GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET`, `GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET` / `GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET`, `CLOUDFLARE_OAUTH_CLIENT_*`, `SUPABASE_OAUTH_CLIENT_*`, MCP OAuth secrets

**Tier 2 — provider APIs (platform):**

- `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `GOOGLE_AI_API_KEY`
- `RESEND_API_KEY`, `RESEND_FROM`, `RESEND_TO`
- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`, `SUPABASE_URL`, `SUPABASE_WEBHOOK_SECRET`, `SUPABASE_DB_WEBHOOK_SECRET`
- `CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN`, `R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID`, `R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY`
- `GITHUB_APP_PRIVATE_KEY`, `GITHUB_TOKEN` (legacy), `MCP_AUTH_TOKEN`, `MCP_SERVICE_URL` (optional)

**Tier 3 — per-user (D1 only, not Wrangler):** `user_secrets`, `user_api_keys`, `mcp_workspace_tokens` — encrypted with `VAULT_MASTER_KEY`.

List live secrets: `npx wrangler secret list -c wrangler.production.toml` (names only).

